# java 8(1.8version)feature

//lambda expression is establish in java 1.8version
1)lambda is anonymous function
2)Anonymous function means no name,no modifier,no return type

# code(we of normal function)
class X{
public static void A(){
    System.out.println("Test");
}
public static void main(String args[]){
    A();
}
}


# code(how to write)
()->{
    //content remain same
    System.out.println("Test");
}

# Benefit of lambda expression
i)Reduce thhe line of code
ii)parallel execution
iii)To write more readable, Maintainable,concise code

# Important rule of lambda
i)If the body of Lambda Expression contain only one statement the curly braces are optional
ii)java compileralso inter the type of variable passed in arguments,hence type is optional.

* Noramal function
import java.util.*;
class prac{
    public static void add(int x,int y){
        System.out.println("sum of the number is "+(x+y));
    }
    public static void main(String args[]){
        add(3,5);
    }
}

* in lambda expression


# Functional interface
i)if the interface contains only one abstract methods then it is Functional interface.
ii)To call the lambda we require funcional interface.
iii)Lambda is used to implement functional interface in very simple and short manner.
